This is what is needed for a simple cyberintegrator service.

SETUP
----
copy jetty-runner.jar, cyberintegrator-service-3.0.0-SNAPSHOT.war, log4j.properties, jetty.xml  and
applicationContext.xml to /home/cyberintegrator

jetty.xml contains the path to the war and applicationContext.xml file.
log4j.properties contains the logging information.
applicationContext.xml contains information about the configuration of the cyberintegrator.

UPSTART
-------
copy cyberintegrator.conf to /etc/init
the cyberintegrator service should be started

SYS V INIT SCRIPTS
-----------------
copy cyberintegrator to /etc/init.d
start cyberintegrator using /etc/init.d/cyberintegrator start
